comment_regular_data.body:
LGTM. Can you rebase?

@jamessan @erw7 care to review?

This looks like it will affect ~~https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/16740~~ https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/22159 (ping @glacambre).

@dstein64 Thanks for your patience, I know this PR has been open for a long time.

This PR conflicts with https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/22159, which provides a generic autocommand event when an OSC sequence is received from the embedded terminal. I'd like to merge #22159 because it can be used to implement the feature in this PR, but also would be very useful for testing (it would enable us to add functional tests for automatic background detection, for instance).

When #22159 is merged then we should be able to re-implement this feature in pure Lua using an autocommand.
